
Passy, 25 May 1778. printed:JA, Diary and Autobiography, 4:116. Replying to Bondfields letters of 12 (above) and 17 May (not found), the Commissioners letter, drafted by Adams, commended Bondfield for his efforts to keep them informed and asked him to send an account of his disbursements and to send future accounts monthly so that the Commissioners could avoid running into debt.
